        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="Emergent Complications of Assisted Reproduction: Expecting the Unexpected" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Keren Tuvia  Baron" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Kemi T.  Babagbemi" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Elizabeth K.  Arleo" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Ashwin V.  Asrani" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Robert N.  Troiano" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="The multimodality imaging findings of emergent maternal complications of assisted reproduction are reviewed, including ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome, ovarian torsion, and ectopic and heterotopi..." /><meta name="Description" content="The multimodality imaging findings of emergent maternal complications of assisted reproduction are reviewed, including ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome, ovarian torsion, and ectopic and heterotopi..." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="With the increasing popularity of assisted reproductive technology (ART), radiologists are more likely to encounter associated complications, especially in an emergency setting. These complications..." /><meta name="Description" content="With the increasing popularity of assisted reproductive technology (ART), radiologists are more likely to encounter associated complications, especially in an emergency setting. These complications..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content="Radiological Society of North America" /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2013-01-01" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="publisher-id" content="125011" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="doi" content="10.1148/rg.331125011" /><meta name="dc.Source" content="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.331125011" /><meta name="dc.Language" content="EN" /><meta name="dc.Coverage" content="world